CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 1, 1947, pg. 29, reads: "Smoky City Guild - Members of the steering committee for the bridge bazaar begin [being] planned by the Smoky City Guild are shown at a recent meeting at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Left to right are Florene Robinson, Billie Goode, seated; Easlor Little, Betty Tibbs and Elsie Brown, standing. The guild event will take place at the Kay Boys Club on the evening of Friday, March 7, and will benefit the fund for a station wagon to be purchased for the Home for the Aged on Lemington Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Smoky City Guild seated from left: Florene Robinson, Billie Goode; standing: Easlor Little, Betty Tibbs, and Elsie Brown posed for meeting in Centre Avenue YMCA
